[11:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'anywhere and then type in load image. And then here, let me load up this image. Next, we just basically need to replace this node with this new load image node here. Now, notice that this'

[11:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'is connected to this latent image node. And right now, this is just an image output. So, we first need to convert this into latent space first. So, I\'m going to double click anywhere here and then type in VAE. And we need to select'

[12:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this VAE encode node. So afterwards, I can connect the pixels here. And then this also takes in the VAE, which we\'ve already loaded up here. So let me connect this node to over here. All'

[12:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'right. Next up, here is where we can choose to draw over the area that we want to edit. All you need to do is rightclick anywhere on this node and then click on open and mask editor. And this allows you to draw over any object'

[12:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
