[13:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a way to transfer the mask over to our latent image before we plug it through this K sampler. So, let\'s double click here and then search for latent mask. And we need to choose this one. set'

[13:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'latent noise mask. Notice that this node should already be available to you because it\'s part of the default Comfy Core nodes. So, let me select this. And then here, I\'m basically going to drag this mask output to this mask input over here. And then finally, I\'m going to'

[13:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'connect the latent over to here. And finally, connect this latent to the K sampler, which would automatically disconnect this one. In fact, we don\'t really need this. So, I can just click on this and then press this button to'

[13:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'bypass it. And then afterwards here we can write something like uh sleeping cat. Now there\'s one more value that we can play with which is this den noiseise setting. This is basically how much of this area do you want to change. One'

[14:07] [scene:talk]
